## Domain Layer Standards

### Entity (Entity) - Rich Domain Model

```java
// ✅ Correct: Rich domain model with business logic inside entity
package com.ai.domain.model;

import com.ai.domain.exception.OrderException;
import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;
import java.util.UUID;

public class Order extends AggregateRoot {

    private final UUID id;
    private OrderStatus status;
    private final List<OrderLine> lines;

    // Private constructor, use factory method
    private Order(UUID id) {
        this.id = Objects.requireNonNull(id);
        this.status = OrderStatus.DRAFT;
        this.lines = new ArrayList<>();
    }

    public static Order create() {
        return new Order(UUID.randomUUID());
    }

    // Business method: place order
    public void place() {
        validateCanPlace();
        this.status = OrderStatus.PLACED;
    }

    // Business method: add order line
    public void addLine(Product product, int quantity) {
        validateCanModify();
        if (quantity <= 0) {
            throw OrderException.invalidQuantity(quantity);
        }
        lines.add(new OrderLine(product.getId(), product.getPrice(), quantity));
    }

    // Status enum
    public enum OrderStatus { DRAFT, PLACED, PAID, SHIPPED, CANCELLED }
}
```

### Value Object

```java
// ✅ Correct: Immutable value object using Java Record
package com.ai.domain.vo;

public record Money(
    BigDecimal amount,
    Currency currency
) {
    public Money {
        Objects.requireNonNull(amount);
        Objects.requireNonNull(currency);
    }

    public Money add(Money other) {
        return new Money(this.amount.add(other.amount), this.currency);
    }
}
```

### Port Interface (Port) - Defined in Domain Layer

```java
// ✅ Correct: Repository port defined in Domain layer
package com.ai.domain.repository;

public interface OrderRepository {
    Optional<Order> findById(UUID id);
    void save(Order order);
}
```

